The paper discusses the state of the art and research gaps in visual affordance and function understanding for robots, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning and deep learning techniques for affordance and functionality learning, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and natural language processing (cs.CL).
